6. Background Service & System Tray Integration
To ensure uninterrupted data synchronization, the application must remain active even when the main window is not visible.
•	Background Execution: Closing ($\times$) or minimizing ($-$) the application window should not terminate the process. Instead, the app must continue running as a background service.
•	System Tray (Taskbar) Icon: * When minimized/closed, a Talliffy icon must remain active in the system tray.
o	Tooltip: Hovering over the icon should display the current sync status (e.g., "Talliffy: Syncing..." or "Talliffy: Up to date").
o	Restore Function: Double-clicking the tray icon or right-clicking and selecting "Open" must restore the application to its fixed-size window.
o	Context Menu: A right-click menu should provide quick options: Open Talliffy, Sync Now, and Exit.
